<IN> COMPUTERS (CPR) </IN>
<TXT>
<p>
   SHL Systemhouse Inc., Ottawa, said it expects to report an
operating loss for its fiscal fourth quarter, ended Aug. 31.
</p>
<p>
   The computer-services company didn't indicate the size of the
anticipated loss. It attributed the shortfall partly to delays in
signing and starting work on major contracts.
</p>
<p>
   Systemhouse also said it expects to record a "major"
restructuring charge of more than 135 million Canadian dollars
(US$102.7 million) in the fourth quarter.
</p>
<p>
   The company's fourth-quarter financial results are due out at the
end of November. In the 1992 fourth quarter, Systemhouse had a net
loss of C$7.4 million, or 18 Canadian cents a share, on revenue of
C$190.4 million.
</p>
<p>
   Systemhouse also said it appointed Paul Damp, 38 years old,
president and chief operating officer. Mr. Damp was previously vice
chairman and chief financial officer. He will succeed James Burns,
46, who was appointed Systemhouse's vice chairman with
responsibility for business development. Mr. Damp will continue to
serve as chief financial officer until a replacement is found.
</p>
