<HL>    Business Brief -- Aviall Inc.:
@  Firm to Post 1st-Period Net
@  In Middle Range of Forecasts </HL>
<DD> 04/20/94 </DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION </SO>
<CO>    AVL </CO>
<IN> AEROSPACE (ARO) </IN>
<TXT>
<p>
   Aviall Inc., Dallas, expects to report first-quarter earnings
roughly in the middle range of analysts' forecasts of five to 10
cents a share.
</p>
<p>
   No comparable per-share figures from a year earlier are available
because the aviation-services company was a unit of Ryder System
Inc. until December, when it was spun off. In the year-earlier
quarter, the company had profit of $1 million on sales of $214.5
million, including a $4.9 million charge for an accounting change.
</p>
<p>
   For the first half, President and Chief Executive Officer
Marshall B. Taylor said results will be down because the company has
less work in progress than it did a year earlier. He also cited
competitive pricing.
</p>
<p>
   But Mr. Taylor said the company is "looking at a strong second
half." Aviall has some price increases due in the second half, and
the company recently renewed or extended engine-overhaul contracts
with its four biggest customers.
</p>
</TXT>
